obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (25628)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25628&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Academy of Scientific`
  line `and Innovative Research Act, 2011.`
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India except the State of Jammu and Kashmir*.`
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 3rd April, 2012 except sub-section (2) of section 5, vide notification No. S.O. 709(E), dated 2nd April, 2012, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  line `26th June, 2013 sub-sec. (2) of section 5, vide notification No. S.O. 1850(E), dated 26th June, 2013, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of`
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (25629)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25629&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, and in all Statutes and Ordinances made thereunder, unless the context`
  line `otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "Academy" means the Academy of Scientific and Innovative Research established under subsection (1) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) "Board" means the Board of Governors of the Academy of Scientific and Innovative Research`
  line `referred to in section 10;`
  line
  line `(c) "Council of Scientific and Industrial Research" means a society registered by the name of the`
  line `Council of Scientific and Industrial Research under the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860);`
  line
  line `(d) "Chairperson" means the Chairperson of the Board appointed under section 12;`
  line
  line `(e) "Chancellor" means the Chancellor of the Academy referred to in section 20;`
  line
  line `(f) "Director" means the Director of the Academy appointed under section 22;`
  line
  line `(g) "distinguished scientists" or "outstanding scientists" of the Council of Scientific and Industrial`
  line `Research means scientists of the Council of Scientific and Industrial Research designated as such;`
  line
  line `(h) "existing Academy" means the Academy of Scientific and Innovative Research established in`
  line `pursuance of the Resolution of the Government of India in the Ministry of Science and Technology,`
  line `Department of Scientific and Industrial Research, Council of Scientific and Industrial Research,`
  line `vide No. 6/1/CSIR-Ac SIR/2010-PPD, dated the 1st July, 2010;`
  line
  line `(i) "Faculty of the Academy" means Academy Professors, Professors of Eminence, Distinguished`
  line `Professors, Outstanding Professors, Senior Professors, Emeritus Professors, Professors, Associate`
  line `Professors, Assistant Professors, visiting faculty, and such other persons as may be appointed for`
  line `imparting instruction or conducting research in the Academy or institutions maintained by the`
  line `Academy and includes the scientists of Council of Scientific and Industrial Research assigned for`
  line `imparting instruction or conducting research;`
  line
  line `(j) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(k) "Statutes and Ordinances" means the Statutes and the Ordinances of the Academy for the time`
  line `being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (25630)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment of Academy of Scientific and Innovative Research.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25630&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such`
  line `date as the Central Government may, by notification, appoint in this behalf, there shall be established for`
  line `the purposes of this Act an Academy to be called the Academy of Scientific and Innovative Research a`
  line `body corporate by such name.`
  line
  line `(2) The headquarters of the Academy shall be at such place as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, specify.`
  line
  line `(3) The Academy may have such number of regional centres and campuses, as it may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(4) The Academy shall have perpetual succession and a common seal with power, subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of property and to contract, and shall by that name,`
  line `sue and be sued.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (25631)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Object of Academy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25631&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The objects of the Academy shall be to—`
  line
  line `(a) disseminate advanced knowledge in science and technology, by providing teaching and`
  line `research facilities in such branches of learning as it may deem fit, particularly in emerging areas and`
  line `such areas as may emerge in future;`
  line
  line `(b) undertake inter-disciplinary studies and research;`
  line
  line `(c) conduct courses in, and integrate into its courses, inter-disciplinary and multi-disciplinary`
  line `areas covering natural sciences, life sciences, mathematical and computational sciences, medical`
  line `sciences, engineering, applied art, humanities, social sciences, law relating to these areas and`
  line `interfaces thereof;`
  line
  line `(d) take appropriate measures for innovations in teaching and learning processes;`
  line
  line `(e) create an ambience for learning and scholarship in advanced science and technology instead of`
  line `exclusively focusing on marks or grades;`
  line
  line `(f) educate and train manpower in scientific and technological fields;`
  line
  line `(g) establish linkages with industries in India and outside India for the promotion of science and`
  line technology;
  line
  line `(h) collaborate, in appropriate areas in the field of science and technology, with reputed`
  line `universities and institutions in India or outside India;`
  line
  line `(i) promote research in science and technology having a bearing on social, economic, cultural,`
  line `intellectual and academic welfare of the people.`
  line
  line `(2) The Academy shall primarily focus on research and imparting instruction in such areas as are not`
  line `ordinarily taught in regular academic universities in India.`
  line
  line `(3) The curricula, pedagogy and evaluation of the Academy shall be innovative and directed towards`
  line `creating highest quality personnel with cross-disciplinary knowledge, aiming to provide leaders in the`
  line `field of science and technology.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (25632)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Relationship of Academy with Council of Scientific and Industrial Research.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25632&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Academy shall be, provided, or, allowed to use, the infrastructure and scientific manpower of the Council`
  line `of Scientific and Industrial Research for teaching and research purposes for mutual benefit.`
  line
  line `(2) The Academy, within two weeks of the commencement of this Act, shall, notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in any other Act, rules, regulations or bye-laws for the time being in force, enter into a`
  line `Memorandum of Understanding with the Council of Scientific and Industrial Research, for the purposes`
  line `of its affiliation with the Academy for the purposes of academics, teaching and award of degrees or`
  line `diplomas, and, the persons pursuing the studies in the Council for award of any degree or diploma, after`
  line `entering of such Memorandum of Understanding, be awarded degrees or diplomas by the said Academy:`
  line
  line `Provided that any person pursuing any academic or research course, before the commencement of this`
  line `Act, in the Council of Scientific and Industrial Research for award of any degree or diploma and`
  line `registered for the said purpose with any other university, may, with the approval of the university with which such person is registered, migrate after such commencement to the Academy established under this`
  line `Act and be registered with the said Academy for grant of the same degree or diploma by the Academy`
  line `established under this Act and such person shall be deemed to have migrated and registered with the`
  line `Academy established under this Act at the same level of study in the university from which such person`
  line migrated.
  line
  line `(3) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall be construed to affect the functions`
  line `or powers of the Council of Scientific and Industrial Research, being discharged or exercised, before the`
  line `commencement of this Act, by the Council or to affiliate with any other university or institution for the`
  line `purposes of academics, teaching and award of degrees or diplomas or for any other purposes necessary`
  line `for pursuing its objects.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (25633)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Declaration of Academy as an institution of national importance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25633&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `It is hereby declared that`
  line `the Academy of Scientific and Innovative Research shall be an institution of national importance.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (25634)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Transfer of assets, liabilities, etc., of existing Academy to Academy established under this Act and other provisions, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25634&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the date of establishment of the Academy,—`
  line
  line `(a) any reference to the existing Academy in any law other than this Act or in any contract or other`
  line `instrument shall be deemed as a reference to the Academy;`
  line
  line `(b) all properties and assets, movable and immovable, of, or belonging to, the existing Academy,`
  line `shall vest in the Academy;`
  line
  line `(c) all rights and liabilities of the existing Academy shall be transferred to, and be the rights and`
  line `liabilities of, the Academy;`
  line
  line `(d) without prejudice to the provisions of clause (c), all debts, obligations and liabilities incurred,`
  line `all contracts entered into and all matters and things engaged to be done by, with or for the existing`
  line `Academy immediately before that date, for or in connection with the purpose of the said existing`
  line `Academy shall be deemed to have been incurred, entered into or engaged to be done by, with or for, the`
  line Academy;
  line
  line `(e) all sums of money due to the existing Academy immediately before that date shall be deemed to`
  line `be due to the Academy;`
  line
  line `(f) all suits and other legal proceedings instituted or which could have been instituted by or against`
  line `the existing Academy immediately before that date may be continued or may be instituted by or against`
  line `the Academy;`
  line
  line `(g) every employee (including those appointed for imparting instruction or conducting research in`
  line `the existing Academy) holding any office under the existing Academy or teaching therein immediately`
  line `before that date shall hold his office in the Academy or continue teaching therein by the same tenure`
  line `and upon the same terms and conditions of service as respects remuneration, leave, provident fund,`
  line `retirement and other terminal benefits as he would have held such office if the Academy had not been`
  line `established and shall continue to do so as an employee of the Academy or until the expiry of the period`
  line `of six months from that date if such employee opts not to be the employee of the Academy within such`
  line period.
  line
  line `(2) Any person pursuing any academic or research course, before the commencement of this Act, in`
  line `the existing Academy for award of any degree or diploma or certificate shall be entitled to pursue such`
  line `academic or research course after the establishment of the Academy under this Act and be registered with`
  line `the said Academy for grant of the same degree or diploma or certificate by the Academy established`
  line `under this Act and such person shall be deemed to have migrated and registered with the Academy`
  line `established under this Act at the same level of study in the existing Academy from which such person`
  line migrated.
  line
  line `(3) Any person, who immediately before the commencement of this Act, had been awarded a degree`
  line `or diploma or certificate for having qualified any course by the existing Academy, shall be entitled to`
  line `award of equivalent degree or diploma by the Academy subject to approval by the Board of the Academy.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947) or in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, absorption of any employee by the Academy in its regular service`
  line `under this section shall not entitle such employee to any compensation under that Act or other law and no`
  line `such claim shall be entertained by any court, tribunal or other authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (25635)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Functions and powers of Academy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25635&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Academy shall discharge its functions and exercise`
  line `the following powers, namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) to provide for instructions and conduct research in such branches of learning like natural`
  line `sciences, life sciences, mathematical and computational sciences, medical sciences, engineering,`
  line `applied art, humanities, social sciences, law relating to these areas and interfaces thereof, and in`
  line `particular, in inter-disciplinary and multi-disciplinary areas of these branches, and in all such areas as`
  line `may emerge in future and other emerging areas of knowledge, as the Academy may from time to time`
  line `determine and make provision for advancement and dissemination of knowledge;`
  line
  line `(ii) to lay administrative standards and structures and decide on all matters of creation of posts,`
  line `laying down standards for recruitment, determining compensation packages, and contractual`
  line arrangements;
  line
  line `(iii) to design its curriculum and pedagogy for award of diplomas or certificates and confer degrees`
  line `or other academic distinctions as it may deem fit;`
  line
  line `(iv) to grant, subject to such conditions as the Academy may determine, diplomas or certificates and`
  line `confer degrees or other academic distinctions on the basis of such methods of evaluation and to hold its`
  line `examinations, as the Academy may, from time to time, determine and to withdraw any such diplomas,`
  line `certificates, degrees or other academic distinctions for good and sufficient cause;`
  line
  line `(v) to frame Statutes and Ordinances and to alter, modify or rescind the same;`
  line
  line `(vi) to organise and undertake extramural studies, training and extension services;`
  line
  line `(vii) to confer honorary degrees or other distinctions;`
  line
  line `(viii) to provide distance education in such branches of learning and to such persons as it may`
  line determine;
  line
  line `(ix) to institute professorships, associate professorships and assistant professorships including`
  line `Academy Professors, Professors of Eminence, Distinguished Professors, Outstanding Professors, Senior`
  line `Professors, Emeritus Professors, or visiting positions and other teaching or academic or other positions,`
  line `required by the Academy and to make appointments to such positions;`
  line
  line `(x) to appoint persons from any other university, or institution, or industry, or persons of eminence`
  line `from appropriate fields of studies, including those outside the country, as Faculty of the Academy;`
  line
  line `(xi) to create administrative, ministerial and other posts and to make appointments thereto;`
  line
  line `(xii) to co-operate or collaborate or associate with any body including, any university or institution,`
  line `or industry, located in India or outside India;`
  line
  line `(xiii) to establish such centres and specialised laboratories or other units for research and instruction`
  line `as may be required;`
  line
  line `(xiv) to set up schools, centres and campuses and function there from or conduct classes from any`
  line `place of its choice, including the premises of laboratories or other centres of the Council of Scientific`
  line `and Industrial Research;`
  line
  line `(xv) to institute and award fellowships, scholarships, studentships, medals and prizes;`
  line
  line `(xvi) to conduct research, advisory and consultancy services with or for any entity, public or`
  line `private, whether in India or outside India, which are in conformity with the spirit and object of the`
  line Academy;
  line
  line `(xvii) to engage scientists of the Council of Scientific and Industrial Research as Faculty in`
  line `imparting instruction and conducting research in the Academy;`
  line
  line `(xviii) to establish, maintain and manage institutions and hostels for residence of students or`
  line `establish and maintain such institutions through the Council of Scientific and Industrial Research or any`
  line `other body;`
  line
  line `(xix) to fix, demand and receive payment of fees and other charges;`
  line
  line `(xx) to determine the standards of admission to the Academy, which may include examination,`
  line `other innovative models of testing or evaluation;`
  line
  line `(xxi) to supervise the residences of the students of the Academy and to make arrangements for`
  line `promoting their health, general welfare, cultural and corporate life;`
  line
  line `(xxii) to lay down conditions of service for all categories of employees, including their code of`
  line conduct;
  line
  line `(xxiii) to regulate and enforce discipline, among the students and employees and to take such`
  line `disciplinary measures in this regard as may be necessary;`
  line
  line `(xxiv) to make arrangements for promoting the health and general welfare of the employees;`
  line
  line `(xxv) to receive grants, benefactions, donations, gifts, bequests and transfer or acquire, hold and`
  line `manage and dispose of any property movable or immovable, including trust and endowment properties`
  line `for the purposes of the Academy:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such grants, benefactions, donations, gifts, bequests and transfer shall be accepted by`
  line `the Academy which in the opinion of the Board involves conditions or obligations opposed to the spirit`
  line `and object of this Act;`
  line
  line `(xxvi) to borrow, on the security of property of the Academy or otherwise, money for the purposes`
  line `of the Academy or utilise its property for such purposes as are in conformity with the spirit and object`
  line `of this Act;`
  line
  line `(xxvii) to do all such other acts and things as may be necessary, incidental or conducive to the`
  line `attainment of all or any of its objects.`
  line
  line `(2) In exercising its powers referred to in sub-section (1), it shall be the endeavour of the Academy to`
  line `maintain an all India character and high standards of teaching and research, and, the Academy shall,`
  line `among other measures which may be necessary for the said purpose, take, in particular, the following`
  line `measures, namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) subject to the provisions of section 9, the admission of students shall be made on merit;`
  line
  line `(ii) continuous evaluation or other innovative methods of evaluation and choice based credit`
  line `system may be introduced and the Academy may enter into agreements with other universities and`
  line `academic institutions in India or outside India for credit transfer and joint degree programmes;`
  line
  line `(iii) innovative courses and programmes of studies shall be introduced with a provision for`
  line `periodic review and restructuring;`
  line
  line `(iv) the imparting of instruction shall be, as far as may be, through use of modern techniques or`
  line technologies;
  line
  line `(v) the systems and structures of the Academy should be flexible to adapt to the requirements of`
  line `multi-disciplinary and inter-disciplinary studies;`
  line
  line `(vi) active participation of students may be ensured in governance of academic matters of the`
  line Academy.
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (25636)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Academy open to all castes, creed, race or class.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25636&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Academy shall be open to all persons,`
  line `of either sex, irrespective of caste, creed, race or class, and it shall not be lawful for the Academy to adopt`
  line `or impose on any person, any test whatsoever of religious belief or profession in order to be entitled to be`
  line `appointed as a Faculty of the Academy or to hold any other office therein, or to be employed therein or to`
  line `be admitted as a student in the Academy or to graduate thereat or to enjoy or exercise any privilege`
  line thereof.
  line
  line `(2) The Academy shall make special provision for the employment or admission of women, persons`
  line `with disabilities or of persons belonging to the weaker sections of the society and, in particular, of the`
  line `Scheduled Castes, the Scheduled Tribes and the other socially and educationally backward classes of`
  line `citizens and any exemption from making such reservation under the proviso to clause (b) of section 4 of`
  line `the Central Educational Institutions (Reservation in Admission) Act, 2006 (5 of 2007) shall not be`
  line `applicable to the Academy:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such special provision shall be made on the ground of domicile.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (25637)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Authorities of Academy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25637&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The following shall be the authorities of the Academy, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) The Board;`
  line
  line `(b) Senate;`
  line
  line `(c) Director;`
  line
  line `(d) Boards of Studies;`
  line
  line `(e) such other authorities as may be declared by the Statutes to be the authorities of the Academy.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (25638)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Composition of Board of Governors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25638&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board referred to in clause (a) of section 10`
  line `shall consist of the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Chairperson of the Board, to be appointed under section 12;`
  line
  line `(b) the Director-General of the Council of Scientific`
  line `and Industrial Research,`
  line `ex officio vice-chairperson;`
  line
  line `(c) the President of the Indian National Science`
  line Academy,
  line `ex officio member;`
  line
  line `(d) the Chairman, Atomic Energy Commission,`
  line `Government of India,`
  line `ex officio member;`
  line
  line `(e) the Chairman, Space Commission,`
  line `Government of India,`
  line `ex officio member;`
  line
  line `(f) the Chairman, University Grants Commission,`
  line `Government of India,`
  line `ex officio member;`
  line
  line `(g) the Finance Secretary in the Ministry of finance`
  line `Government of India,`
  line `ex officio member;`
  line
  line `(h) the heads of three premier institutions in the field of`
  line `imparting education in Science and Technology,`
  line `members to be nominated`
  line `under section 13;`
  line
  line `(i) four distinguished scientists or academicians of`
  line `global eminence, of which two should be from reputed`
  line `institutions outside India,`
  line `members to be nominated`
  line `under section 13;`
  line
  line `(j) three eminent industrialists or technologists, members to be nominated`
  line `under section 13;`
  line
  line `(k) four distinguished scientists or outstanding`
  line `scientists or Directors of laboratories of Council of`
  line `Scientific and Industrial Research,`
  line `members to be nominated`
  line `under section 14;`
  line
  line `(l) the Director of the Academy, ex officio member.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson shall ordinarily preside over the meetings of the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board may evolve its own procedure for the purpose of conducting its meetings and`
  line `transacting business therein.`
  line
  line `(4) The Associate Director in charge of administration of the Academy shall be the Secretary of the`
  line Board.
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (25639)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Appointment of Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25639&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson shall be appointed by the President of the`
  line `Council of Scientific and Industrial Research, on the recommendation of the selection committee`
  line `constituted under sub-section (2):`
  line
  line `Provided that the Director-General of the Council of Scientific and Industrial Research, being the`
  line `ex officio Vice-Chairperson , as referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 11, shall act as the`
  line `Chairperson until the first Chairperson is selected and appointed in accordance with the provisions of this`
  line `Act:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no person shall be selected and appointed as Chairperson unless such person is`
  line `an Indian citizen.`
  line
  line `(2) The selection committee referred to in sub-section (1) shall consist of four eminent scientists or`
  line `technologists of international repute, as may be nominated by the President of the Council of Scientific`
  line `and Industrial Research.`
  line
  line `(3) At least two eminent scientists or technologists of international repute nominated under`
  line `sub-section (2) shall be from the heads of international societies, academies, or similar organisations in`
  line `the field of science and technology.`
  line
  line `(4) The selection committee referred to in sub-section (2) shall--`
  line
  line `(a) be constituted within six months before the completion of tenure of the incumbent as the`
  line `Chairperson of the Board;`
  line
  line `(b) submit its recommendation at least three months before the completion of the tenure of the`
  line `incumbent Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(5) The selection committee may evolve its own procedure for the purposes of meetings and making`
  line `recommendations under sub-section (1) including making recommendations in respect of a person who`
  line `has not applied for the post of Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(6) Three members of the selection committee referred to in sub-section (1) shall form quorum for the`
  line `meeting of the committee.`
  line
  line `(7) The Chairperson shall exercise such other powers and perform such other functions as may be`
  line `assigned to him by this Act or the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (25640)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Nomination of distinguished scientists or academicians of global eminence, eminent industrialists or technologists and heads of three premier institutions in the field of imparting education in science and technology.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25640&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The heads of three premier institutions in the field of imparting`
  line `education in science and technology, referred to in clause (h), the distinguished scientists or academicians`
  line `of global eminence referred to in clause (i), and eminent industrialists or technologists referred to in`
  line `clause (j), of sub-section (1) of section 11, shall be nominated, by the President of the Council of`
  line `Scientific and Industrial Research.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (25641)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Nomination of distinguished scientists or outstanding scientists of Council of Scientific and Industrial Research or Directors of Council of Scientific and Industrial Research laboratories.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25641&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The nomination of distinguished scientists or outstanding scientists of the Council of Scientific and`
  line `Industrial Research or Directors of Council of Scientific and Industrial Research laboratories, referred to`
  line `in clause (k) of sub-section (1) of section 11 shall be made by the Governing Body of the Council of`
  line `Scientific and Industrial Research.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (25642)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Allowances payable to members of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25642&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The members of the Board shall be entitled to such`
  line `allowances, if any, from the Academy, as may be provided for, in the Statutes but no member other than the Director of the Academy referred to in clause (l) of sub-section (1) of section 11, shall be entitled to`
  line `any salary by reason of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (25643)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Term of office of members of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25643&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this section, term of`
  line `office of the Chairperson or any other nominated member of the Board shall be four years, being one term`
  line `of the Board and they shall not be eligible to be re-appointed as Chairperson or nominated as a member,`
  line `as the case may be.`
  line
  line `Explanation I.--The period of term of office of the Chairperson or any other nominated member of`
  line `the Board [other than ex officio Vice-Chairperson and ex officio members and nominated members under`
  line `clause (k) of sub-section (1) of section 11] of the existing Academy shall be counted for the purposes of`
  line `this sub-section.`
  line
  line `Explanation II.--For the removal of doubt it is hereby declared that a person who held the office of a`
  line `member shall not be eligible to be re-appointed as a member but may be appointed as the Chairperson in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that an outgoing member of the Board shall, unless or otherwise directed, continue in office`
  line `until another person is appointed, or, as the case may be, nominated as a member in his place.`
  line
  line `(2) In the event of vacancy in the office of the Chairperson, by reason of his death or resignation or`
  line `otherwise, the Vice-Chairperson shall act as the Chairperson until a new Chairperson is appointed in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act to fill the vacancy and enter upon his office:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person appointed due to a vacancy in the office of Chairperson under sub-section (2),`
  line `shall be eligible to be appointed as Chairperson in accordance with the provisions of this Act only for one`
  line `term in addition to the period for which he was appointed to fill the vacancy of Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(3) In the event of vacancy in the office of a nominated member under clauses (h), (i), (j) and (k) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 11 by reason of his death or resignation or otherwise, the vacancy shall be filled`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person nominated under sub-section (1) of section 11 due to a vacancy in the office of`
  line `the member, such person shall be eligible to be nominated only for one term as member in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of this Act, in addition to the period for which he was nominated to fill the vacancy.`
  line
  line `(4) The term of office of an ex officio member shall continue as long as he holds the office by virtue`
  line `of which he is a member.`
  line
  line `(5) One-fourth of the members, being distinguished scientists or outstanding scientists or Directors of`
  line `laboratories of the Council of Scientific and Industrial Research nominated under clause (k) of sub-section`
  line `(1) of section 11 shall retire every year and new members shall be nominated in their place in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that, notwithstanding anything contained in this sub-section, the members, being`
  line `distinguished scientists or outstanding scientists of the Council of Scientific and Industrial Research or`
  line `Directors of the Council of Scientific and Industrial Research laboratories nominated under clause (k) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 11, immediately after the commencement of this Act for the first time, may hold`
  line `office for such period, as may be specified in their nomination and provisions of this sub-section shall not`
  line `be applicable to such nominated members.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (25644)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Powers of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25644&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Board shall be responsible for`
  line `the general superintendence, direction and control of the affairs of the Academy and shall exercise all the`
  line `powers of the Academy not otherwise provided for by this Act, the Statutes and the Ordinances, and shall`
  line `have the power to review the acts of the Senate.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Board shall have the powers to—`
  line
  line `(a) take decisions on questions of policy relating to the administration and working of the`
  line Academy;
  line
  line `(b) institute courses of study at the Academy;`
  line
  line `(c) make Statutes;`
  line
  line `(d) institute and appoint persons to academic as well as other posts in the Academy;`
  line
  line `(e) consider and modify or cancel or rescind Ordinances;`
  line
  line `(f) consider and pass resolutions on the annual report, the annual accounts and the budget`
  line `estimates of the Academy for the next financial year, together with a statement of its development`
  line plans;
  line
  line `(g) approve investments in infrastructure of the Academy in any land or building;`
  line
  line `(h) exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as may be conferred or imposed`
  line `upon it by this Act or the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall also have the power to appoint such committees of one or more persons as it`
  line `considers necessary for exercise of its powers and the performance of its duties and hold enquiries under`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (25645)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title Senate.
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25645&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Senate shall consist of the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Director, ex officio, who shall be the Chairperson of the Senate;`
  line
  line `(b) all Associate Directors, ex officio members;`
  line
  line `(c) all Deans of the Academy, ex officio members;`
  line
  line `(d) two Professors from each area of study represented by the Boards of Studies of the Academy,`
  line `as may be nominated by the Board, ex officio members;`
  line
  line `(e) two scientists of the Council of Scientific and Industrial Research, who being the youngest in`
  line `age; and recipient of Shanti Swaroop Bhatnagar Award; and who are also Faculty of the Academy, as`
  line `may be nominated by the Director-General of the Council of Scientific and Industrial Research;`
  line
  line `(f) two scientists of the Council of Scientific and Industrial Research, who being the youngest in`
  line `age; and recipient of CSIR-Young Scientist Award; and who are Faculty of the Academy, as may be`
  line `nominated by the Director-General of the Council of Scientific and Industrial Research;`
  line
  line `(g) three Directors or distinguished scientists or outstanding scientists of the Council of Scientific`
  line `and Industrial Research laboratories, nominated by its Director-General;`
  line
  line `(h) three persons, not being the employees of the Academy or the Council of Scientific and`
  line `Industrial Research, to be nominated by the Chancellor in consultation with the Director from`
  line `amongst educationists of repute, one being from each of the fields of science, engineering and social`
  line sciences;
  line
  line `(i) such other members of the staff as may be laid down in the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(2) The tenure of the nominated members under clauses (d) to (h) of sub-section (1) shall be two`
  line `years:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Senate shall not, at any time, have less than fifty per cent. of its members from the`
  line `Council of Scientific and Industrial Research scientists teaching in the Academy.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (25646)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Powers of Senate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25646&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Statutes and the Ordinances, the`
  line `Senate of the Academy shall have the control and general regulation, and be responsible for the`
  line `maintenance, of standards of instruction, education and examinations in the Academy and shall exercise`
  line `such other powers and perform such other duties as may be conferred or imposed upon it by the Statutes`
  line `and Ordinances.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (25647)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Chancellor of Academy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25647&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson of the Board shall be the Chancellor of the`
  line Academy.
  line
  line `(2) The Chancellor shall ordinarily preside at the Convocations of the Academy.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (25648)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Director of Academy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25648&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The Director shall be the principal academic and executive officer of the`
  line `Academy and shall be responsible for the administration of the Academy and imparting instruction,`
  line `research and maintenance of discipline.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (25649)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Appointment and duty of Director of Academy, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25649&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Director shall be appointed, by`
  line `the President of the Council of Scientific and Industrial Research, on the recommendation of the selection`
  line `committee constituted under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2) The selection committee referred to in sub-section (1) shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) the Chairperson of the Board;`
  line
  line `(b) the Vice-Chairperson of the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) the President of the Indian National Science Academy;`
  line
  line `(d) the Chairman, Atomic Energy Commission, Government of India;`
  line
  line `(e) the Chairman, Space Commission, Government of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The selection committee referred to in sub-section (2) shall--`
  line
  line `(a) be constituted within six months before the completion of tenure of the incumbent as the`
  line Director;
  line
  line `(b) submit its recommendation at least three months before the completion of the tenure of the`
  line `incumbent Director.`
  line
  line `(4) The selection committee may evolve its own procedure for the purposes of meetings and making`
  line `recommendations under sub-section (1) including making recommendations in respect of a person who`
  line `has not applied for the post of Director.`
  line
  line `(5) Three members of the selection committee referred to in sub-section (1) shall form quorum for the`
  line `meeting of the committee:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall be selected or nominated as Director unless such person is an Indian`
  line citizen.
  line
  line `(6) It shall be the duty of the Director that the decisions taken by the Board are implemented.`
  line
  line `(7) The Director shall submit an annual report and accounts of the Academy to the Board.`
  line
  line `(8) The Director shall exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as may be assigned to`
  line `him by this Act or the Statutes or the Ordinances.`
  line
  line `(9) The term of the Director shall be five years.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (25650)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Associate Directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25650&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Associate Directors of the Academy shall, be appointed by the`
  line `Director with the approval of the Board, from amongst Professors of the Academy or scientists of the`
  line `Council of Scientific and Industrial Research engaged in academic activity in the Academy, for such`
  line `period, and on such terms and conditions, as may be laid down by the Statutes, and, shall exercise such`
  line `powers and perform such duties as may be assigned to them by this Act or the Statutes or by the Director.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may assign any other designation for the Associate Directors, for the purpose of`
  line `administrative convenience or academic efficiency.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (25651)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Powers of other authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25651&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The constitution and powers of Board of Studies shall be such`
  line `as may be provided in the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(2) The powers, including the financial powers and duties of authorities, officers and other`
  line `functionaries of the Academy shall be as provided by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (25652)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Funds of Academy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25652&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Academy shall maintain and retain a fund to which shall be`
  line credited--
  line
  line `(a) all fees (including tuition fees) and other charges received by the Academy;`
  line
  line `(b) all monies received by the Academy by way of grants, gifts, donations, benefactions, bequests`
  line `or transfers;`
  line
  line `(c) monies for projects undertaken by the Academy;`
  line
  line `(d) income from investment made by the Academy or from any other source;`
  line
  line `(e) the funds received from the Council of Scientific and Industrial Research, by way of loan or`
  line otherwise;
  line
  line `(f) all monies received by the Academy in any other manner or from any other source.`
  line
  line `(2) All monies credited to the fund of the Academy shall be deposited in such banks or invested in`
  line `such manner as the Academy may, with the approval of the Board, decide.`
  line
  line `(3) The fund shall be applied for meeting,--`
  line
  line `(a) the salaries, allowances and other remuneration of the Chairperson, members of the Board or`
  line `Faculty, officers and other employees or members of the committees set up by the Academy;`
  line
  line `(b) the expenses of the Academy in the discharge of its functions or exercise of its powers under`
  line `section 8;`
  line
  line `(c) the expenses on objects of, and for purposes authorised by, this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) All expenditure of the Academy shall be within the framework of a budget approved by the`
  line Board.
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (25653)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title Accounts.
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25653&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Academy shall maintain proper and separate accounts giving therein the`
  line `details of all receipts in, and, expenditure from, such fund and other relevant particulars.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts referred to in sub-section (1) shall be prepared and got audited before the expiry of`
  line `six months from the end of each financial year.`
  line
  line `(3) The Academy shall submit to the Board and the Council of Scientific and Industrial Research, the`
  line `accounts referred to in sub-section (1) duly audited under section 27 and signed by the Director, Associate`
  line `Director in charge of Finance and Associate Director in charge of Administration.`
  line
  line `(4) The Council of Scientific and Industrial Research referred to in sub-section (3), the Board and any`
  line `other person appointed by them in connection with the audit of the accounts of the Academy shall have`
  line `the right to demand the production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and`
  line `papers and to inspect any of the offices of the Academy.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (25654)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Audit of accounts and its publication.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25654&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The accounts of the Academy shall, without`
  line `prejudice to the provisions contained in the Comptroller and Auditor-Generals (Duties, Powers and`
  line `Conditions of Service) Act, 1971 (56 of 1971), be audited by auditors who may be appointed by the`
  line `Board for the term of one year and such auditors shall be eligible for re-appointment.`
  line
  line `(2) No person shall be eligible to be appointed as an auditor under sub-section (1) unless he is a`
  line `chartered accountant as defined in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Chartered Accountants`
  line `Act, 1949 (38 of 1949), and who has obtained a certificate of practice under sub-section (1) of section 6`
  line `of that Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The accounts of the Academy shall, after the completion of the audit under sub-section (1) and`
  line `submission thereof to the Board and the Council of Scientific and Industrial Research be published on the`
  line `website of the Academy.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (25655)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title Statutes.
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25655&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Statutes of the Academy shall be enacted by the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section (1), the Senate may make`
  line `recommendations for enactment of Statutes to the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board may, from time to time, make new Statutes or may amend or repeal or rescind the`
  line `Statutes with effect from such date as it may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (25656)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Matters to be provided by Statutes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25656&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Statutes may`
  line `provide for all or any of the matters considered necessary by the Board for functioning of the Academy`
  line `within the framework of this Act, including the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the conferment of degrees and diplomas;`
  line
  line `(b) the constitution, powers and functions of the Board of Studies;`
  line
  line `(c) the tuition fee and other fees to be charged;`
  line
  line `(d) the institution of fellowships, scholarships, medals and prizes;`
  line
  line `(e) the term of office and the method of appointment of officers of the Academy;`
  line
  line `(f) the qualification of Faculty of the Academy (other than the scientists of the Council of`
  line `Scientific and Industrial Research engaged in the service of the Academy), officers and other staff of`
  line `Academy:`
  line
  line `Provided that the scientists of the Council of Scientific and Industrial Research engaged in the`
  line `service of the Academy shall be governed by the qualifications specified by the Council and nothing`
  line `contained in this Act shall be construed to disqualify them from undertaking the service of the`
  line `Academy or engaging them as Faculty of the Academy;`
  line
  line `(g) the classification, the method of appointment and the determination of the terms and`
  line `conditions of service of Faculty, officers and other staff of the Academy;`
  line
  line `(h) the provision of insurance fund, provident fund and other retirement benefits, for the benefit`
  line `of the Faculty, officers and other staff of the Academy;`
  line
  line `(i) the constitution, powers and duties of authorities of the Academy;`
  line
  line `(j) the establishment and maintenance of hostels;`
  line
  line `(k) the conditions of residence of students of the Academy and the levying of fees for residence in`
  line `the hostels and of other charges;`
  line
  line `(l) the allowances to be paid to the Chairperson and other members of the Board and any`
  line `committee constituted by the Academy;`
  line
  line `(m) the meetings of the Board, the Senate, or any committee, the quorum at such meetings and the`
  line `procedure to be followed in the conduct of their business;`
  line
  line `(n) any other matter which may be required or necessary for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (25657)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title Ordinances.
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25657&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act and the Statutes, the Ordinances of the`
  line `Academy may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the admission of the students;`
  line
  line `(b) the courses of study;`
  line
  line `(c) the conditions under which students shall be admitted and shall be eligible for degrees,`
  line `diplomas and certificates and to the examinations of the Academy, and shall be eligible for the`
  line `degrees, diplomas and certificates;`
  line
  line `(d) the conditions of award of the fellowships, scholarships, medals and prizes;`
  line
  line `(e) the condition and mode of appointment and duties of examining bodies, examiners and`
  line moderators;
  line
  line `(f) the conduct of examinations;`
  line
  line `(g) the maintenance of discipline among students of the Academy;`
  line
  line `(h) any other matter which by this Act or the Statute, is to be, or, may be, provided for by the`
  line Ordinances.
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise provided in this section, Ordinances shall be made by the Senate.`
  line
  line `(3) All Ordinances made by the Senate shall have the effect from such date as it may direct, but every`
  line `Ordinance so made shall be submitted, as soon as may be, to the Board and shall be considered by the`
  line `Board in its subsequent meeting.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board shall have the power by resolution to modify or cancel or rescind any of the`
  line `Ordinances and such Ordinances shall, from the date of such resolution stand modified accordingly or`
  line `cancelled or rescinded, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (25658)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Review of functioning of Academy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25658&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a review of the functioning of the`
  line `Academy once in every four years by persons of eminence to be appointed by the Council of Scientific`
  line `and Industrial Research.`
  line
  line `(2) The Academy shall meet the expenses for conducting the review under sub-section (1) and upon`
  line `receipt of the report of such review, the Board may take appropriate action.`
  line
  line `(3) In addition to the review under sub-section (1), the Board may conduct review of functioning of`
  line `administrative and academic wings of the Academy, in such manner and at such intervals, as may be`
  line `provided in the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (25659)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title Appointments.
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25659&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `All appointments of the staff of the Academy (except appointment of the`
  line `Director), shall be made in accordance with the procedure laid down in the Statute, by--`
  line
  line `(a) the Board for the academic staff;`
  line
  line `(b) the Director, in any other case.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (25660)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Conditions of service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25660&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every employee of the Academy shall be appointed on contractual`
  line `basis under a written contract, which shall be lodged with the Academy and a copy of which shall be`
  line `furnished to the employee concerned:`
  line
  line `Provided that all scientists and other employees of the Council of Scientific and Industrial Research`
  line `engaged in the service of the Academy shall be governed by the service conditions, rules and regulations`
  line `of the Council of Scientific and Industrial Research.`
  line
  line `(2) The Academy shall have a flexible compensation system which recognises performance, as laid`
  line `down in the Statutes, to bring the best talent in the Academy:`
  line
  line `Provided that the scientists of the Council of Scientific and Industrial Research--`
  line
  line `(a) engaged in the service of the Academy; and`
  line
  line `(b) who draw their salary from the Council,`
  line
  line `shall be eligible for such allowances or honorarium, as may be determined by the Statute.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (25661)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title Arbitration.
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25661&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any dispute arising out of a contract between the Academy and any of its`
  line `employees shall, at the request of the employee concerned or at the instance of the Academy, be referred`
  line `to a Tribunal of Arbitration consisting of one member appointed by the Director, one member nominated`
  line `by the employee, and such two arbitrators shall appoint the third arbitrator who shall act as the presiding`
  line arbitrator.
  line
  line `(2) The arbitration under sub-section (1) shall be governed by the Arbitration and Conciliation Act,`
  line `1996 (26 of 1996).`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (25662)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Resignation, removal and suspension of Chairperson and other Member or Director.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25662&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `The Chairperson or any Member of the Board other than ex officio Members of the Board or Director`
  line `may, by notice in writing under his hand addressed to the President of the Council of Scientific and`
  line `Industrial Research, resign his office:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson or such Member or Director shall, unless he is permitted by the President`
  line `of the Council of Scientific and Industrial Research to relinquish his office sooner, continue to hold office until the expiry of three months from the date of receipt of such notice or until a person duly appointed as`
  line `his successor enters upon his office or until the expiry of his term of office, whichever is the earliest.`
  line
  line `(2) The President of the Council of Scientific and Industrial Research may remove from office the`
  line `Chairperson or any Member of the Board or the Director, who--`
  line
  line `(a) has been adjudged an insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(b) being the Director has engaged at any time, during his term of office, in any paid`
  line `employment; or`
  line
  line `(c) has been convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the Central Government, involves`
  line `moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(d) has become physically or mentally incapable of acting as such Chairperson or Member or`
  line `Director; or`
  line
  line `(e) is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court; or`
  line
  line `(f) has acquired such financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially the exercise of`
  line `his functions as such Chairperson or Member or Director; or`
  line
  line `(g) has so abused his position as to render his continuance in office prejudicial to the public`
  line `interest; or`
  line
  line `(h) has been guilty of proved misbehavior; or`
  line
  line `(i) has such other disqualifications as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Chairperson or a Member of the Board`
  line `or the Director shall not be removed from his office on the grounds specified in clause (f) or clause (g) or`
  line `clause (h) of sub-section (1), except by an order made by the President of the Council of Scientific and`
  line `Industrial Research after an inquiry made in this behalf in which such Chairperson or Member or Director`
  line `has been informed of the charges against him and given a reasonable opportunity of being heard in`
  line `respect of those charges.`
  line
  line `(4) In the event of inquiry instituted under sub-section (2), the President of the Council of Scientific`
  line `and Industrial Research may suspend such Chairperson or Member or Director against whom inquiry has`
  line `been instituted for a period not exceeding six months if it is considered necessary in public interest.`
  line
  line `(5) The President of the Council of Scientific and Industrial Research may, by rules, regulate the`
  line `procedure for the inquiry referred to in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(6) In case any nominated member under clause (k) of sub-section (1) of section 11 in the Board`
  line `incurs any of the disqualifications under clauses (a) to (i) of sub-section (1), such nominated member`
  line `shall not be eligible to be nominated as such and his nomination as nominated member shall be revoked`
  line `by those who nominated such member.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (25663)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title Meetings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25663&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `The meetings of the Board, Senate, or other committees constituted by the Academy`
  line `may be held using contemporary tools of information and communication technologies (including videoconferencing) without the members necessarily having to be physically present.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (25664)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate acts or proceedings of Board, Academy or any other body.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25664&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `No act of the Board or the Academy or any other body set up under this Act or the Statutes, shall`
  line `be invalid merely by reason of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or defect in the constitution thereof; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the selection, nomination or appointment of a person acting as a member`
  line `thereof; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in its procedure not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (25665)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700&sectionId=25665&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_31_82_00001_201213_1517807327700
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions,`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under this section after the expiry of three years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under sub-section (1) shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised`
  line `in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the order or both Houses agree that the order should not be made, the order shall thereafter have effect`
  line `only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification`
  line `or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that order.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
